1 Disc losure Act. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are
2 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
3 Commission for any expenses incurred by the Political Subdivisions
4 Enforcement Division. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon
5 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
6 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
7 Enterprise Services for approval and payment. No later than January
8 31, 2016, and every year thereafter, the State Treasurer shall
9 transfer to the General Revenue Fund of the state any monies in the
10 fund in excess of One Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($150,000.00)
11 Four Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($450,000.00). If at any time
12 the amount of money in the fund is less than One Hundred Thousand
13 Dollars ($100,000.00), the Executive Director of the Commission may
14 order that there be no further enforcement by the Political
15 Subdivisions Enforcement Division until the amount of money in the
16 fund is more than One Hundred Thousand Dollars ($100,000.00).
17 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
18 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
19 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
20 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
